					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I was confused by your use of &quot;half way through the scanline&quot;. Split screen scrolling in NES games works by changing the scroll value mid-screen, usually in the 64-dot (21-cycle) period between one scanline and the next. Doing so mid-screen allows scrolling each horizontal strip separately. A game would have to change the scroll value mid-scanline in order to have vertical strips, and MMC5 is the only mapper I know of on NES that's capable of that.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

